cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD, cs.CE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), scientific computing (cs.SD), and computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper describes a novel neural network architecture for learning the behavior and properties of complex many body physical systems, specifically atomic potential energy surfaces for use in molecular dynamics simulations. The paper's focus on neural networks and machine learning, as well as its application to scientific computing and computational engineering, make these sub-categories the most likely candidates.
